dy":"Born November 8, 1867 New York; married George B. Huntington in Indiana 1887 at age nineteen. Bore six children between 1888 and 1902, three of whom died young (Walter 1893 infant; Olive age six in 1900; Ruth age two in 1900)."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"amanda-ferris-1867"},"TD0263":{"id":"TD0263","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Henry","middle_name":"Augustus","last_name":"Huntington","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Henry Augustus Huntington"},"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1816,"month":8,"day":26,"city":"Coventry","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1895,"month":11,"day":26,"city":"Sugar Creek Township","county":"Shelby","state":"Indiana","country":"United States","cause":"Paralysis"},"residence":{"city":"Sugar Creek Township","county":"Shelby","state":"Indiana","country":"United States"},"burial":{"plot_notes":"Center Cemetery, Shelby County Indiana — alongside wife Sarah Ann Edwards Huntington and parents."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":7,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"TD0260","mother_id":"I01146"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I01149","date_year":1850,"date_month":4,"date_day":5,"location_county":"Shelby","location_state":"Indiana","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1895,"children_ids":["TD0273","TD0274","TD0275","TD0276","TD0277","TD0278","TD0279","TD0280"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["connecticut_migration","indiana_migration","ohio_migration","politician"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Three-state migration before age five, Connecticut to Indiana","body":"Henry Augustus Huntington was born August 26, 1816 in Coventry Connecticut, three years before his parents' 1819 westward move. The family went first to Lebanon Ohio, then about a year later to Connersville Indiana, and in 1821 finally settled 'in the wilds of Sugar Creek township' in Shelby County Indiana, where Henry grew up. The whole multi-step journey unfolded before he reached his fifth birthday."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Died exactly one month after wife Sarah","body":"Henry and his wife Sarah Ann Edwards Huntington lived on the same Sugar Creek farm from 1852 until both died in 1895. Sarah died October 26, 1895; Henry died November 26, 1895 of paralysis — exactly one month later, to the day. They had been married forty-five years."},{"number":3,"category":"politics","header":"Thirteen-year Sugar Creek Township trustee","body":"Henry served as Sugar Creek Township trustee for thirteen years — the longest single elected term in his community's documented late-nineteenth-century record. He was a Democrat and described in his 1895 obituary simply as 'an honest' man. The trustee role oversaw township roads, poor-relief, and school funding through the years of the agrarian populist movement that reshaped Indiana politics."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"henry-huntington-1816"},"I01149":{"id":"I01149","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Sarah","middle_name":"Ann","last_name":"Huntington","maiden_name":"Edwards","married_names":["Huntington"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Sarah Ann Edwards Huntington"},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1825,"month":12,"day":22,"county":"Miami","state":"Ohio","coun